╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                    SHIP'S LIBRARY                             ║
║              "Know thy tools, know thyself"                   ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

ARIA's voice echoes softly:

"Welcome to the Ship's Library, crew member. This archive contains
the accumulated knowledge of generations of engineers who built
and refined the tools you now use.

Every command has a story. Every tool was forged to solve a real
problem. Understanding their origins will help you wield them
with greater purpose.

The archives are organized by category:

  BASICS     - Foundation tools: reading, listing, navigating
  SEARCH     - Finding needles in haystacks: grep, find
  PIPELINES  - The art of flowing data: pipes, sort, cut
  TRANSFORM  - Shaping text to your will: sed, awk, xargs
  CONCEPTS   - Deeper patterns: regex, scripting, processes

Some sections remain locked until you prove your skills in the
relevant ship sectors. Knowledge is earned here, not given.

To access an archive, use:

  ./scripts/lore.sh <topic>

For example:

  ./scripts/lore.sh grep

May these records serve you well on your journey."

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  "The tools we use shape the thoughts we think."               │
│                                    — Ken Thompson, circa 1973   │
